Typo: in the user code example, I think the second should be in rather than out.<p>This is pretty cute - looks useful in practice.  I think you can slightly enhance the probability of the compiler making the result efficient by using a switch statement, like:<p><pre><code>    goto setup1;
    got_value:
    switch (value) {
       setup1: ...setup 1...; goto setup2;
       case 1: ...; break;
    }
</code></pre>
etc.<p>In C++, you could do something fairly equivalent with lambdas, without having to involve the &quot;evil&quot; preprocessor.
